OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F336A1781954391
OL,3,CCouncil overturns climate pledge under
OL,4,Cnew Reform leadership
OL,6,FReform took control of the council
OL,7,Ffrom Labour by winning 58 out of 63
OL,8,Fseats at the local elections in May.
OL,10,FCouncil leader Karl Johnson put
OL,11,Fforward the motion to overturn
OL,12,Fprevious commitments. He told the
OL,13,FCouncil on 17 June: "Too much time
OL,14,Fspent on virtue signalling and gesture
OL,15,Fpolitics, not enough time on improving
OL,16,Fresidents' lives. This now comes to an
OL,17,Fend."
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G2/5
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BYorks News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,337,330,260,120,000,100
PN,33603
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F336A1781954391
OL,3,CCouncil overturns climate pledge under
OL,4,Cnew Reform leadership
OL,6,FHe added that in his opinion the
OL,7,Fmotion was not about denying climate
OL,8,Fchange, saying: "This is about moving
OL,9,Fforward in a more realistic, grounded
OL,10,Fand impactful way. Every penny spent
OL,11,Fon net zero takes away everything from
OL,12,Four residents.
OL,14,F"With council tax set this year at
OL,15,Fanother 4.99% we need to put our
OL,16,Fresidents first."
OL,18,FGreen Party councillor Kate Dodd
OL,19,Fopposed the motion, which she
OL,20,Fdescribed as a "classic example of
OL,21,Fgesture politics."
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G3/5
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BYorks News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,337,330,260,120,000,100
PN,33604
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F336A1781954391
OL,3,CCouncil overturns climate pledge under
OL,4,Cnew Reform leadership
OL,6,FShe said: "This is no joke. This is
OL,7,Fserious. To suggest that this is not
OL,8,Fan emergency, to suggest that it's not
OL,9,Fsomething that urgently needs to be
OL,10,Ftackled is frankly irresponsible."
OL,12,FCouncillor Dodd also said that
OL,13,FCouncillor Johnson, a former
OL,14,FConservative Party member, had
OL,15,Fpreviously voted in favour of the
OL,16,Fclimate emergency declaration.
OL,18,FLabour councillor Mohammed Ayub added:
OL,19,F"I've yet to see any evidence of what
OL,20,Ffinancial savings this proposal will
OL,21,Fdeliver."
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G4/5
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BYorks News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,337,330,260,120,000,100
PN,33605
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F336A1781954391
OL,3,CCouncil overturns climate pledge under
OL,4,Cnew Reform leadership
OL,6,FMembers of environmental group Just
OL,7,FTransition Wakefield gathered outside
OL,8,Fahead of the meeting.
OL,10,FGroup chair Stuart Boothman said: "We
OL,11,Fare really disappointed in the council
OL,12,Ftaking this action. It is clear that
OL,13,Fthe emergency has got worse. It hasn't
OL,14,Fgone away."
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G5/5
